One thing to keep in mind is that, while the interaction between the player and NPC on the surface appears to the player as an exchange, internally you don't have to make it so. In other words, as long as it looks like the transaction has taken place, you don't need to worry about things like the NPC actually receiving money or actually making a decision based on that money. It just needs to &quot;make the right noise&quot; in the output text.

A simple solution could be a command like this:

[code:73a2ju3k]  &lt;command&gt;
    &lt;pattern&gt;give money to bartender&lt;/pattern&gt;
    &lt;script&gt;
      msg (&quot;He slips the money into the cash register&#46; \&quot;Here you go,\&quot; he says, handing you your martini&#46;&quot;)
      AddToInventory (Martini)
    &lt;/script&gt;
  &lt;/command&gt;[/code:73a2ju3k]
It might seem a bit lame. It might not be what you want this time. But sometimes, it's all you really need.

XanMag can help you do this in the GUI~Editor, so here's the code stuff of it:

------------

there's 4 built-in randomization functions for you to use:

<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/functions/getrandomint.html">http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/ ... omint.html</a><!-- m --> (GetRandomInt)
<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/functions/getrandomdouble.html">http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/ ... ouble.html</a><!-- m --> (GetRandomDouble)

<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/functions/corelibrary/diceroll.html">http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/ ... eroll.html</a><!-- m --> (DiceRoll)

<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/functions/corelibrary/randomchance.html">http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/ ... hance.html</a><!-- m --> (RandomChance)

------------

using 'RandomChance' with one of the other randomization functions works very well for stuff like this, a quick brief sample example:

the 'GetRandomInt' selects the item, and then the 'RandomChance' determines whether you actually get that selected item or not.

[code:36d153bc]&lt;object name=&quot;short_sword&quot;&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;alias&quot; type=&quot;string&quot;&gt;short sword&lt;/attr&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;parent&quot; type=&quot;object&quot;&gt;item_drop_container&lt;/attr&gt;
&lt;/object&gt;

&lt;object name=&quot;hand_axe&quot;&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;alias&quot; type=&quot;string&quot;&gt;hand axe&lt;/attr&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;parent&quot; type=&quot;object&quot;&gt;item_drop_container&lt;/attr&gt;
&lt;/object&gt;

&lt;object name=&quot;club&quot;&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;alias&quot; type=&quot;string&quot;&gt;club&lt;/attr&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;parent&quot; type=&quot;object&quot;&gt;item_drop_container&lt;/attr&gt;
&lt;/object&gt;

&lt;object name=&quot;dagger&quot;&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;alias&quot; type=&quot;string&quot;&gt;dagger&lt;/attr&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;parent&quot; type=&quot;object&quot;&gt;item_drop_container&lt;/attr&gt;
&lt;/object&gt;

&lt;object name=&quot;short_bow&quot;&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;alias&quot; type=&quot;string&quot;&gt;short bow&lt;/attr&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;parent&quot; type=&quot;object&quot;&gt;item_drop_container&lt;/attr&gt;
&lt;/object&gt;

&lt;object name=&quot;item_drop_container&quot;&gt;
  &lt;attr name=&quot;weapon_class_list_1&quot; type=&quot;objectlist&quot;&gt;
    &lt;value&gt;short_sword&lt;/value&gt;
    &lt;value&gt;hand_axe&lt;/value&gt;
    &lt;value&gt;club&lt;/value&gt;
    &lt;value&gt;dagger&lt;/value&gt;
    &lt;value&gt;short_bow&lt;/value&gt;
  &lt;/attr&gt;
&lt;/object&gt;

&lt;function name=&quot;weapon_class_1_drop&quot;&gt;
  selected_item = ObjectListItem (item_drop_container&#46;weapon_class_list_1, GetRandomInt (0, ListCount (item_drop_container&#46;weapon_class_list_1) - 1))
  if (RandomChance(95)) {
    msg (&quot;You got &quot; + selected_item&#46;alias)
    selected_item&#46;parent = player
  } else {
    msg (&quot;You got nothing, sorry&quot;)
  }
&lt;/function&gt;[/code:36d153bc]
